**v0.0.6**

Write pipelining + concurrent operation support

  - WRITE handler returns UNSTABLE4 for unstable writes, enabling write pipelining — client sends many writes concurrently without waiting. For DATA_SYNC4/FILE_SYNC4 requests, calls Sync() on the filesystem and only returns the requested stability if sync succeeds. Otherwise downgrades to UNSTABLE4. Never lies about durability.
  - COMMIT handler calls Sync() on the underlying filesystem (if supported) to flush buffered data to stable storage.
  - Worker cleanup() now acquires lock before iterating file/lister maps, fixing a race condition with concurrent request handlers.
  - Worker locking changed from Mutex to RWMutex. Read-only operations (GetFile, IsRemovedFile, GetFileByClientSeqID) use RLock for concurrent access.
  - Request/Response channel buffers increased from 50 to 256.


**v0.0.5**

Increase FATTR4 maxread/maxwrite from 32KB to 1MB

Channel negotiation (v0.0.4) set session limits to 1MB but FATTR4_MAXREAD/MAXWRITE were still hardcoded to 32KB. NFS clients use these attributes to determine wsize/rsize, overriding the channel limits.


**v0.0.4**

Negotiate channel attributes in CREATE_SESSION

  - Server was echoing back client-proposed channel sizes unchanged,
  - causing Linux NFS clients to stay at 32KB wsize/rsize. Now enforces minimum 1MB request/response sizes for adequate throughput.


**v0.0.3**

Add lease tracking and enforcement

  - Client leases tracked per-client with 90s timeout (RFC 7530)
  - RENEW operation renews lease timer
  - LOCK implicitly renews lease on success
  - Background goroutine expires stale leases every 30s
  - Expired clients get NFS4ERR_EXPIRED on lock attempts
  - Released locks cleaned up on lease expiry


**v0.0.2**

Add NFSv4 file locking (LOCK/LOCKT/LOCKU)

  - Advisory byte-range locking per RFC 7530 Section 9.
  - Read locks (shared), write locks (exclusive), conflict detection,
  - grace period for lock reclamation on server restart.


**v0.0.1**

- Prep as dependency
